<h1>About Paul</h1>

<div class="row">
	<div class="col-md-4"><%= image_tag("#{PortfolioImage::ROOT_PATH}about/portrait-oahu.jpg", :alt => "Portrait of Paul Bogard", :class => "img-fluid portrait bordered") %></div>
	
	<div class="col-md-8">

		<p>Paul Bogard is the Lead Engineer for KC-46 Aircrew Training Systems with the United States Air Force at Wright-Patterson Air Force Base, Ohio. He has been performing acquisition of full flight simulators as a systems engineer since 2009.  He holds a Bachelor of Science in Computer Engineering from <%= link_to("Rose-Hulman Institute of Technology", "http://www.rose-hulman.edu/", target: "_blank") %> and a Master of Science in Computer Engineering from <%= link_to("Wright State University", "http://www.wright.edu/", target: "_blank") %>.</p>

		<p>Paul enjoys travel, airports, airplanes, trains, interesting roads and intersections, and nearly anything else related to transportation. He currently lives in Beavercreek, Ohio.</p>

	</div>
</div>

